invariant multiprocessing_extra117.SharedMemory_name_len_12:
  description: "multiprocessing.shared_memory.SharedMemory.__name__.__len__() == 12 — 'SharedMemory' = 'Shared'=6+'Memory'=6=12; two equal halves of 6 chars each; SharedMemory.__name__.__eq__('SharedMemory')==True; SharedMemory.__qualname__.__len__()==12 (tied: __qualname__==__name__ for top-level class); SharedMemory provides a named shared memory block allocated by the OS that can be mapped into multiple processes simultaneously; it allocates a POSIX shared memory segment on Unix or a named file mapping on Windows; compare: ShareableList.__name__.__len__()==13 (1 more: 'ShareableList'=13 vs 'SharedMemory'=12); SharedMemory.__module__.__len__()==29 ('multiprocessing.shared_memory'=29: module is 17 chars longer than class name); SharedMemory.__mro__.__len__()==2; SharedMemory.__bases__[0].__name__=='object'; no prior multiprocessing spec covered SharedMemory class attributes (extra25 only covered the module __name__); first standalone SharedMemory.__name__ length invariant in mpshm117 namespace; wave 259; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: shared_memory.SharedMemory.__name__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 12

invariant multiprocessing_extra117.SharedMemory_module_len_29:
  description: "multiprocessing.shared_memory.SharedMemory.__module__.__len__() == 29 — 'multiprocessing.shared_memory' = 'multiprocessing.'=16+'shared_memory'=13=29; SharedMemory.__module__.__eq__('multiprocessing.shared_memory')==True; the module name len=29 also equals the value already confirmed in extra25 as shared_memory.__name__.__len__()==29 (the module attribute and the class __module__ agree because SharedMemory is defined at the top level of that module); SharedMemory.__name__.__len__()==12; ShareableList.__module__.__len__()==29 (tied: both classes are in the same module); SharedMemory.__mro__.__len__()==2; 'multiprocessing.shared_memory'=29 is longer than 'multiprocessing.reduction'=25 (covered in extra116: 4 chars shorter; 'reduction'=9 vs 'shared_memory'=13, diff=4); first standalone SharedMemory.__module__ length invariant in mpshm117 namespace; wave 259; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: shared_memory.SharedMemory.__module__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 29

invariant multiprocessing_extra117.ShareableList_name_len_13:
  description: "multiprocessing.shared_memory.ShareableList.__name__.__len__() == 13 — 'ShareableList' = 'Shareable'=9+'List'=4=13; ShareableList.__name__.__eq__('ShareableList')==True; ShareableList.__qualname__.__len__()==13 (tied with __name__); ShareableList is a mutable sequence stored in a SharedMemory block; it supports only fixed-size built-in types (int, float, bool, bytes, None, str with fixed max length); it wraps a SharedMemory block and stores items packed as C structs; compare: SharedMemory.__name__.__len__()==12 (1 less than ShareableList=13); ShareableList.__module__.__len__()==29 (tied with SharedMemory); ShareableList.__mro__.__len__()==2 (tied with SharedMemory; both inherit directly from object); ShareableList.__init__.__code__.co_qualname.__len__()==22 (1 more than SharedMemory.__init__ co_qualname len=21; consistent 1-char difference); first standalone ShareableList.__name__ length invariant in mpshm117 namespace; wave 259; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: shared_memory.ShareableList.__name__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 13

invariant multiprocessing_extra117.SharedMemory_init_co_qualname_len_21:
  description: "multiprocessing.shared_memory.SharedMemory.__init__.__code__.co_qualname.__len__() == 21 — 'SharedMemory.__init__' = 'SharedMemory.'=13+'__init__'=8=21; SharedMemory.__init__.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__('SharedMemory.__init__')==True; SharedMemory.__init__ takes self, name, create, size as positional params (co_argcount==4); co_varnames.__len__()==10 (most in spec: includes platform-specific locals like h_map, last_error_code, p_buf for the Windows handle and mapping, as well as track, stats, temp_name); compare: ShareableList.__init__ co_qualname len=22 (1 more: 'ShareableList'=13 vs 'SharedMemory'=12, diff=1 propagates to co_qualname length); 'SharedMemory.'=13-char prefix vs 'ShareableList.'=14-char prefix; SharedMemory.__name__.__len__()==12; SharedMemory.__module__.__len__()==29; first standalone SharedMemory.__init__ co_qualname length invariant in mpshm117 namespace; wave 259; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: code_attrs
  kind: python_call_eq
